node.text:
load up on guns,
bring your friends.
it’s fun to lose
and to pretend.

and just take my heart out.
that’d make it better.
i won't be sorry,
better late than never.

drop a hairdryer into my bath,
shocks like that make me laugh.
it's fun to laugh when you're sad.
be happy,
come on let me be happy.

but when you touch me like this
and you hold me like that.
i just have to admit,
that it's all coming back to me.

i wouldn't hesitate
to smile while you suffocate and die.
and that would be just fine,
and what a lovely time.

what’s the point of living
if my heart gets broken?
driving on the road,
waiting for head-on collision.

i don't wanna waste your time.
go 'head and live your life,
i could be yours tonight.

and i am done with my
graceless heart.
so tonight
i’m gonna cut it out
and restart.

you make my life worthwhile
with the slightest smile,
or destroy me
with a barely perceptible whisper.

you pull me by my hair
so i don't go nowhere.
tell me you love me,
but you treat me like i’m never there.

fuck being all alone in back of the classroom.
stop calling up my phone,
trying to say that i’ve been out of line,
when all i ever asked was to go to the bathroom.

could you be my first time?
eat me up like apple pie.
make me not wanna die,
love me rough and let me fly.

i go red hot like a demon,
i go ghost for no damn reason.
a song that goes on and on.

isn't it strange?
how people can change,
from strangers to friends,
friends into lovers,
and strangers again.

she eat me like a cannibal.
then she wanna kiss me, 
i'm like nah, that's impractical.

wasted times i spent with someone else,
she wasn't even half of you.

people like to tell you
what you're gonna be.
it's not my problem if
you don't see what i see.
and i don't give a damn
if you don't believe.

can't we be seventeen?
that's all i want to do.
if you could let me in, 
i could be good with you.

sneaky, greedy, money seeking.
always peeping, fucking creeping.

you are the moon, stars, and sunshine of my life !
you brighten up my cloudy, grey days . . .
no need for rules anymore, chaos has won.
damnation never felt so cleansing.
i would hug all my friends if they weren't friends with you ٩(｡•́‿•̀｡)۶
are you tired of me yet? i'm a little sick right now but i swear when i'm ready i will fly us out of here.
